---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Skill Evolution | Codex Frontend Lab" description="How frontend skill instructions evolved across experiment versions.">
  <section class="container page-head">
    <p class="eyebrow">Instruction Design</p>
    <h1>How the Skill Was Tuned</h1>
    <p>
      The `frontend-design` skill was evolved through tightly scoped mutation axes: typography identity, section depth,
      reliability gates, interaction outcomes, and domain-specific copy pressure.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="container section-grid">
    <article class="card">
      <h2>Mutation Discipline</h2>
      <p>Each version changes one primary rule set so quality shifts remain attributable.</p>
    </article>
    <article class="card">
      <h2>Quality Gates</h2>
      <p>Rules target common failures: repetitive structure, weak hierarchy, shallow interaction, and noisy styling.</p>
    </article>
    <article class="card">
      <h2>Benchmark Fairness</h2>
      <p>The shared prompt remains untouched to avoid prompt drift inflating perceived improvements.</p>
    </article>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
